Do you want to know what happened to dnd? Why it feels like it's falling apart at the seams right now? Why quality is dropping off a cliff? Why they're firing all of the talented people who are responsible for making 5e so special?
Corporate ownership. 
Dnd isn't a game to them. It's an asset.

They don't care about making a good game that could sustain a healthy and steadily growing player base. 
That doesn't excite shareholders. That doesn't make literally more money than exists on the planet. 
Every bad decision they make is rooted in the corpos calling the shots and not the creators

Unfortunately, the golden age of dnd is over. Just remember that it didn't die of natural causes. It was crushed to death by unrealistic shareholders and corporate greed

Now we wait to see what comes next

Recently gave a friend advice that I realized is maybe helpful for other people in #witchsky

When it comes to hexing exes, I think you really have to sit and ask what's more important to you right now: revenge & retaliation or keeping clean of them as much as possible.

Because doing magic on another person creates a tie between you and them for as long as the magic is in action. So if you do a cord-cutting and then a hex, you've undone the cord-cutting. If you do a hex and then a cord-cutting, you've undone the hex.

Obviously, you can wait, give the hex time to work, and then cut ties when the hex is done. But that does mean sitting with that link existing for that whole time. If you're hexing them because they stalked you, for example, this isn't gonna make them any less obsessed with you.

This is not advice on which you should do. If you think hexing is your right choice, go for it. The only reason I bring it up is because I see people mess up their own cord cutting with this shit ALL THE TIME. If you want the ex to let go of you, you have to let go of them too.

Obviously this depends on exact formula. My wife pointed out the possibility of wrapping a quick-acting hex into the cord-cutting itself. And cord-cutting is just literally not an option for some people. But IN GENERAL, I think these are things to be considered.

i looked into the pathless conlang and here's what i found so far, a thread üëáüßµ

first of all, there are some holes yet that i am trying to understand

unfortunately all the voice over has a level of filtering on top of it, some distorting the speaking more than others (looking at you mother eagle cof cof)

naturally, this is a preliminary work and possibly meanings and structures may evolve and change

so far that's what i could confirmüëá

[vo.ka.ra] = mortal, person/people, human

[sha.zo/sha.zoo] = world, universe?

[kas.k√™] = stupid, fool

[ki.va] = destroy, eliminate (broad: cease to exist)

[k√™] = no, stop (negative/contrary meaning)*

[ma.sa] = path

*[k√™] shows up as suffix in some words too, as in [ma.sa.k√™] = pathless

at the end of the game i noticed there's a variation of [ma.sa] (that i have yet to confirm) that is translated as "salvation" and it's interesting to think how these different ideas (path and salvation) have a similar meaning (even if it's wrong let me cope ok)

i also could determine some names/titles

[sha.lo] = hunter

[ki.va.toor] = godslayer

[toor] (reads the same as in godslayer [toor]) = tall ones

[shu.va] = eagle

there's still a lot to unpack like the 'ji', 'sa.hir' and 'ja' that appears a lot and that i suspect they serve as verbs but also maybe pronouns? i am really not sure and further digging is necessary, i will see more in the future

that has GROSSLY misinterpreted some historical figures and religious literature.  There's a little bit of a sec cult going on!

So six months ago, we're making our way through this giant mega dungeon.  She'd worked on this map for over a year at this point.  It was massive.  

So we find a hidden

BDSM room.  But notably, the cult worships these historical figures that this BDSM room belonged to as gods.  Nothing in there had been touched after the cult moved in, it was treated as a shrine.

So I messaged my lovely wife and told her "I'm stealing all the dildos in here.  I have a plan."

Cut to our last game.  @liesandperfidy.bsky.social , @hockeybabbler.bsky.social , our friend nick and I finally entire the final boss room.  Everything has been building to here.  The angry grandpa ghost in my sword (don't ask) is really pleased that we're about to dish out some justice.

Speeches are made, quips are had and just as the towering elven death knight begins to villain monologue, magic pulsing in his hand....

I charge at him and toss a two foot schlong that smacks him in the face, making sure he knows who it belonged to.  Guys, all of this is to say that for the past

six months, I've been DREAMING of the look on their faces.  The confirmation that yes, I had been planning this for six months and somehow managed to not spoil it to anyone.  

It might be my greatest ttrpg moment if I'm being real.  Anyway, if you've made it this far, Magnus did nothing wrong.

A friend of mine asked how #MarkCarney would be different for the #LPC than #Trudeau, as he was an advisor for Trudeau and made no change as far as he's aware. Why is Carney a better choice than #Poilievre? So I answered as follows:

I see #MarkCarney as a return to center left. Trudeau was further left, pulling the #liberalparty with him. Carney is an #economist and highly qualified in his field, I see him as having a much better understanding of how government policy affects the country than any of the other leaders,

I'm very put off by #Poilievre. He campaigns on liberal bashing first and foremost, and plays heavily into identity politics. When someone starts using terms like #woke, it's an immediate no from me. I have too many people I care about that would be considered "woke", including myself,
#PierrePoilievre rose in the conservative party after a lot of infighting and a really nasty leadership race-- several of his opponents accused him of being too far right and accepting of extremists

#Poilievre was the solution and counter balance to the further left policies of #Trudeau, but #Carney is a different breed of #liberal and as an outsider, he doesn't have the same taint to him as long term #politicians.

As far as #Carney as an advisor to the #Trudeau government, he had zero say in policy. Advisors give input on policy they're being consulted about, but whether that input is taken is up to the #politicians soliciting the advice.

#Freeland broke away and resigned from cabinet over the budget that #Trudeau pushed as she saw it as fiscally irresponsible, there was also palpable tension within the party as members wanted #Trudeau to step down months before he finally did.

A change in leadership is a change in direction. This was the same when the #CPC went from #Scheer to #Otoole. Otoole was a red tory, more centre, but his leadership was short as the CPC made a very poor choice to put forward a non confidence vote to dissolve the 1 year old #minoritygovernment--
--- this was unpopular across #Canada and resulted in more infighting in the CPC when we ended up with virtually the exact same minority government.

At any rate, all this to say, I believe that the #Carney government will be very different from #Trudeau as he has already decreased the bloated cabinet, #cancelledcarbontax, and is commiting to a #middleclasstaxcut.
I also like that the campaign is already running on a positive note, I have always loathed #attackads and frankly, some of the ads the CPC is running right now are just ridiculous--
-- the red tinted one of Carney raising his eyebrows #hesjustlikejustin with ominous music is only topped by the comic book style ad with the slogan #SneakyMarkCarney--

these are reactionary #attackads because they had not decided what they would bash him about, though the campaign people have seemingly decided to settle on his former companies head office moving to New York angle.

I also resent hearing that #Canadaisbroken-- it is not. #Canada, like the rest of the Western world, is currently experiencing a massive population distribution shift---we have more people retiring and retired than we do to fill these empty positions because people stopped having as many kids.

This has led to gaps in pretty much every profession and industry, gaps hastily attempted to be filled by #immigration without taking into account that the #agingpopulation is still living in their homes which has exacerbated the #housingcrisis.

We will be running a #deficit for some time until our population evens out, but if we have to run a deficit, we need to make sure it's a responsibly managed one, but does not claw back heavily on the people services.

Housing needs to remain a priority, as well as fiscal responsibility. I think #Carney as an #economist is the right person to bring balance to Canada's needs, and has the business savvy and people skills to grow our #economy through new #tradedeals.
Many politicians, including #Trudeau, have more idealistic visions of how #Canada should be run without the expertise to understand why parts of their vision may not be reasonably attainable.

#Carney brings the expertise, and based on some of what I understand from his book Values, I think that expertise will be good to bring us back to the center. When he has #conservatives supporting him, I think he's a good choice for everyone.

#Canada #Canadaisnotbroken #Canadasky #CanPoli #LPC

How much foreign aid is actually spent domestically rather than overseas?

In a new article for @ourworldindata.org, @hannahritchie.bsky.social and I examine how this differs between countries, how it has changed over time, and what this means for supporting developing countries. (1/9)

In 2023, 22% of foreign aid was spent domestically within rich donor countries, not overseas.

This domestic spending has more than tripled from $14 billion to $48 billion since 2010. As a share of total aid, it has increased considerably from 10% to 22%. (2/9)

You can see that the largest cost in recent years has been for hosting refugees. This is primarily due to the surge in refugees from Ukraine following Russia's invasion.

Refugee hosting costs only count as foreign aid for the first year, so this figure may decrease again soon. (3/9)

Australia and Luxembourg don't report costs of hosting refugees as aid, arguing these don't help poor countries develop. On the other hand, hosting refugees does address urgent humanitarian needs of foreign citizens who've been forcibly displaced, even if the money is spent domestically. (4/9)

In 2023, three countries spent over half of their foreign aid domestically: Poland, Ireland, and Czechia. Nearly all of this was used for hosting refugees, predominantly from Ukraine.

In our home countries, the UK and the Netherlands, it accounted for one-third and one-quarter, respectively. (5/9)

In nearly all countries, the costs of hosting refugees dominate domestic aid spending. However, there are notable exceptions. Hungary, for instance, spent 41% of its aid budget on providing scholarships to international students studying within its borders. (6/9)

One might expect 2023 to be an outlier due to the number of Ukrainian refugees seeking safety from the war. But was 2023 truly anomalous?

The trends vary by country. Domestic spending has steadily increased in the US and risen even more dramatically in the UK. (7/9)

Nevertheless, in absolute numbers, *overseas* aid has been rising.

However, in many major donor countries, it notably dropped in 2023: Germany, France, and the United States are examples. The United Kingdom stands out: its overseas spending in 2023 was 60% lower than in 2019. (8/9)

In a world that‚Äôs more generous, aid activities like hosting refugees do not have to come at the cost of lifesaving programs overseas. But in a world with a shrinking aid budget, this tension will only increase.

You can read our article here: ourworldindata.org/foreign-aid-... (9/9)
